</augment_code_snippet>

The problem is that your `.flow` div is not properly closed. It should wrap all the content that needs flow spacing. Fix it like this:

<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/mushroom-guide.html" mode="EDIT">
```html
<section class="mushroom-guide section">
 <div class="wrapper">
 <div class="flow">
 <h2 class="section-title">Get to know your mushrooms</h2>
 <select name="" id="">
 <option value="all">Season: All</option>
 <option value="spring">Spring</option>
 <option value="summer">Summer</option>
 <option value="winter">Winter</option>
 <option value="fall">Fall</option>
 </select>
 <select name="" id="">
 <option value="all">Type: All</option>
 <option value="edible">Edible</option>
 <option value="toxic">Toxic</option>
 </select>
 <!--grid of Mushrooms-->
 <div class="grid-auto-fit">
 <!-- mushroom cards -->
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>
```
</augment_code_snippet>

The `.flow` class works by adding margin to adjacent sibling elements (`> * + *`), so all elements that need flow spacing must be direct children of the `.flow` container.
