2. **Fixed double function call**: You were calling `filterCards()` twice - once inside `startViewTransition()` and once after it, which was causing conflicts.

3. **Added browser support check**: Now it checks if `document.startViewTransition` is supported before using it.

````javascript path=01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/script.js mode=EXCERPT
// Add unique view transition names to each card for smooth animations
cards.forEach((card, index) => {
 const mushroomId = `mushroom-${index + 1}`;
 card.style.viewTransitionName = `mushroom-card-${mushroomId}`;
});

function updateFilters(e) {
 const filterType = e.target.name || e.target.id;
 currentFilters[filterType] = e.target.value;

 // Use View Transition API if supported, otherwise fallback to regular filtering
 if (document.startViewTransition) {
 document.startViewTransition(() => filterCards());
 } else {
 filterCards();
 }
}
````

## Why View Transitions Now Work:

1. **Unique Identity**: Each card has its own `view-transition-name`, so the browser can track individual cards during transitions
2. **Proper API Usage**: The View Transition API is called correctly with the filtering function as a callback
3. **Browser Compatibility**: Falls back to regular filtering if the browser doesn't support view transitions
4. **Single Execution**: `filterCards()` only runs once per filter change

Now when you filter the mushroom cards, you should see smooth animations as cards move to their new positions in the grid, rather than just instantly appearing/disappearing!
