## The Problems:
1. **Animation defined but not applied** - You had the `@keyframes fade-out` defined but it wasn't being used anywhere
2. **Missing fade-in animation** - You only had fade-out but no corresponding fade-in
3. **View transitions conflicting** - Your filtering was using view transitions instead of the fade animation

## The Solutions:

### 1. Added CSS Animation Classes
<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/style.css" mode="EXCERPT">
```css
@layer animations {
 .fade-out {
 animation: fade-out 0.3s ease-out forwards;
 }

 .fade-in {
 animation: fade-in 0.3s ease-in forwards;
 }
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

### 2. Implemented JavaScript Fade Animation (Per Your Preference)
<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/script.js" mode="EXCERPT">
```javascript
function fadeOutAndFilter() {
 // Fade out all cards first
 cards.forEach(card => {
 if (!card.hidden) {
 card.style.opacity = '0';
 card.style.transition = 'opacity 0.3s ease-out';
 }
 });

 // After fade out completes, filter and fade in
 setTimeout(() => {
 filterCards();

 // Fade in visible cards
 cards.forEach(card => {
 if (!card.hidden) {
 card.style.opacity = '1';
 card.style.transition = 'opacity 0.3s ease-in';
 }
 });
 }, 300); // Wait for fade out to complete
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

## How It Works Now:
1. **When filters change** → Cards fade out smoothly (0.3s)
2. **After fade-out completes** → Filtering logic runs to show/hide cards
3. **Visible cards fade in** → Smooth transition back to full opacity

## Test Your Animation:
